(2, 1, '2015-03-23 16:06:57', '2015-03-23 16:06:57', 'This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Sample Page', '', 'draft', 'open', 'closed', '', 'sample-page', '', '', '2015-04-06 07:16:20', '2015-04-06 07:16:20', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(5, 1, '2015-03-02 13:05:21', '2015-03-02 10:05:21', 'To create shortcuts for these Windows functions follow the next steps:\n\n1. From the <strong>Context menu</strong> on the Desktop or in any folder select <strong>New -&gt; Shortcut.</strong>\n\n2. In the Location field type:\n<ul>\n  <li>For <strong>Shutdown:</strong>\n<code>shutdown.exe -s -t 00</code></li>\n  <li>For <strong>Restart</strong>\n<code>shutdown.exe -r -t 00</code></li>\n  <li>For <strong>Workstation lock</strong>\n<code>Rundll32.exe User32.dll,LockWorkStation</code></li>\n  <li>For <strong>Sleep</strong>\n<code>rundll32.exe powrprof.dll,SetSuspendState Sleep</code></li>\n  <li>For <strong>Hibernation</strong>\n<code>rundll32.exe powrprof.dll,SetSuspendState</code></li>\n</ul>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/create-shortcut.jpg" alt="Create Shortcut" width="447" height="327" />\n\n3. Press Next and type the shortcut name.\n\n4. After it you can use the shortcut by <strong>doubleclicking</strong> on it or by assigning a <strong>keyboard shortcut</strong> to it (that can be done in its Properties <strong>Shortcut key</strong> field).\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-61" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/shortcut-properties.jpg" alt="Shortcut Properties" width="376" height="525" />', 'Shutdown, Restart, Lock, Sleep and Hibernate Shortcuts', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shutdown-restart-lock-sleep-and-hibernate-shortcuts', '', '', '2015-03-02 13:05:21', '2015-03-02 10:05:21', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=3', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(6, 1, '2015-03-01 14:11:20', '2015-03-01 14:11:20', 'When you open, save or browse for a file, Windows opens a "<strong>Common file dialog box</strong>" containing a few shortcuts in left side pane which is called "<strong>Places Bar</strong>" and the shortcuts are called "<strong>Places</strong>".\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nTo customize these follow the next steps:\r\n\r\n1. Type <strong>regedit</strong> in RUN dialog box and press Enter. Go to:\r\n<pre>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies</pre>\r\n2. Right-click on <strong>Policies</strong> key and select <strong>New -&gt; Key</strong>. It\'ll create a new key, give it name <strong>comdlg32</strong>. Now again right-click on this new "comdlg32" key and select <strong>New -&gt; Key</strong> and give the new key name <strong>Placesbar</strong>. So the final key path would be:\r\n<pre>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\comdlg32\\Placesbar</pre>\r\n3. Select <strong>Placesbar</strong> key and in right-side pane, create a new <strong>String</strong> value <strong>Place0</strong> and set its value to your desired path. You can set it to a drive like C: or you can set it to a particular folder like D:\\Wallpapers. You can also use some predefined values to put system elements in Places Bar:\r\n<pre>MyComputer\r\nMyDocuments\r\nMyMusic\r\nMyPictures\r\nMyNetworkPlaces\r\nMyFavorites\r\nCommonDocuments\r\nCommonMusic\r\nCommonPictures\r\nDesktop\r\nPrinters\r\nRecent\r\nProgramFiles</pre>\r\nYou can set up to <strong>5 places</strong>. So to change other default places, create new String values <em>Place1, Place2, Place3 </em>and<em> Place4</em> and set their value to your desired path.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-23" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/registry-branch-for-places.png" alt="Registry Branch for Places" width="507" height="159" />\r\n\r\n4. Now you\'ll see your desired places in common file dialog box. No restart needed.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-25 size-full" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/places-bar-after-customization-in-windows-xp.png" alt="Places Bar after customization in Windows XP" width="563" height="417" />\r\n\r\n<em>Source: <a title="How to Customize Default Places Bar in Windows Common File Dialog Box?" href="http://www.askvg.com/how-to-customize-default-places-bar-in-windows-common-file-dialog-box/" target="_blank">How to Customize Default Places Bar in Windows Common File Dialog Box?</a></em>', 'Customize Places Bar in File Dialog Box', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'customize-places-bar-in-file-dialog-box', '', '', '2015-04-05 20:57:00', '2015-04-05 20:57:00', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=5', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(64, 1, '2015-03-02 13:58:37', '2015-03-02 13:58:37', '1. Go to the <strong>Registry</strong> editor:\n<pre>Win+R -&gt; "regedit"</pre>\n2. Go to the following branch:\n<pre>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Control Panel\\International</pre>\n3. Find the key with this name:\n<pre>iFirstDayOfWeek</pre>\n4. Change its value to a digit in the <strong>[0-6]</strong> range which converts to the <strong>[Monday-Sunday]</strong> range.\n\n5. The changes should apply immediately after the value change.\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-65" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/international-registry-branch.jpg" alt="International Registry Branch" width="558" height="259" />', 'Change the First Day of the Week in the Calendar', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'change-the-first-day-of-the-week-in-the-calendar', '', '', '2015-03-02 13:58:37', '2015-03-02 13:58:37', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=64', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(69, 1, '2015-03-02 14:16:51', '2015-03-02 14:16:51', '1. Go to the <strong>Registry</strong> editor:\n<pre>Win+R -&gt; "regedit"</pre>\n2. Go to the following branch:\n<pre>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Command Processor</pre>\n3. Find the key or create a new one (as a <strong>String</strong> key) with this name:\n<pre>Autorun</pre>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-70" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cmd-default-directory.jpg" alt="CMD Default Directory" width="554" height="299" />\n4. Change its value to a string with this format:\n<pre>cd /d [path]</pre>\nwhere the <strong>[path]</strong> is a folder path\n\n5. The changes should apply the next time you open the Command Line window (cmd.exe).', 'Command Line - Set the Default Startup Directory', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'command-line-set-the-default-startup-directory', '', '', '2015-03-02 14:16:51', '2015-03-02 14:16:51', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=69', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(72, 1, '2015-03-02 14:20:04', '2015-03-02 14:20:04', 'This post will show some <strong>Windows Command Line (CMD)</strong> tricks I will have experience with.\r\n\r\n1. To <em>navigate to a folder</em> quickly it is possible to type the <strong>"cd"</strong> command and <strong>drag\'n\'drop</strong> the folder from other explorer (default Windows Explorer or Total Commander).\r\nIf you want to go to a folder on a different drive add the "/d" argument:\r\n<pre>cd /d [drag\'n\'drop a folder]</pre>\r\n2. Press <strong>F7 </strong>to open the <em>commands list</em>.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-394" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cmd-commands-list.jpg" alt="CMD commands list" width="677" height="343" />\r\n\r\n3. To go to the <em>root directory</em> type\r\n<pre>cd\\</pre>\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-971" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cmd-tricks-root-dir.png" alt="CMD tricks, Go to root dir" width="677" height="343" />', 'Command Line Tricks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'command-line-tricks', '', '', '2015-04-04 06:45:54', '2015-04-04 06:45:54', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=72', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2015-03-02 17:39:23', '2015-03-02 17:39:23', 'There isn\'t default settings that allow this functionality.\r\nIt is necessary to install the <a title="Classic Shell" href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/classicshell/files/" target="_blank"><strong>Classic Shell</strong></a> application:\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-75 size-full" title="Classic Shell Toolbar" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/classic-shell-toolbar.jpg" alt="Classic Shell Toolbar" width="327" height="147" />\r\n\r\nThen use these steps:\r\n\r\n1. Go to the <strong>Windows Explorer</strong>. There should be a toolbar under the address bar.\r\n\r\n2. Open the <strong>Classic Explorer Settings</strong>. On the toolbar should be the Shell button on the right.\r\n\r\n3. On the <strong>Basic Settings</strong> tab in the <strong>Navigation pane style</strong> setting select the <strong>Windows XP Simple</strong> option.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-76 size-full" title="Classic Shell Settings" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/classic-shell-settings.jpg" alt="Classic Shell Settings" width="688" height="461" />\r\n\r\n4. Press OK. Close and open the Explorer window.\r\n\r\n5. Try to click on the left tree branches. They should expand automatically on one click.', 'Windows Explorer - Expand Tree with One Click', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'windows-explorer-expand-tree-with-one-click', '', '', '2015-03-24 15:04:05', '2015-03-24 15:04:05', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=74', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(78, 1, '2015-03-02 17:45:49', '2015-03-02 14:45:49', '1. Win+R -&gt; "services.msc".\n\n2. Go to <strong>Shell Hardware Detection</strong> service properties.\n\n3. Set <strong>Startup type</strong> to <strong>Disabled</strong> and stop the service.\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/shell-hardware-detection-properties.jpg" alt="Shell Hardware Detection Properties" width="600" height="532" /></p>', 'Disable \'Do you want to scan and fix drive\' message for USB drives', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'disable-do-you-want-to-scan-and-fix-drive-message-for-usb-drives', '', '', '2015-03-02 17:45:49', '2015-03-02 14:45:49', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=78', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(80, 1, '2015-03-02 21:20:50', '2015-03-02 18:20:50', '<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Windows 7</span></h3>\r\n<p>To set sharing options use these steps:</p>\r\n<p>1. Go to the folder properties and to the <strong>Sharing</strong> tab.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-83" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-tab.jpg" alt="Sharing Tab" width="377" height="487" /></p>\r\n<p>2. Press the <strong>Share</strong> button and select the <strong>users</strong> you want to share the folder contents with.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-users.jpg" alt="Sharing Users" width="628" height="458" /></p>\r\n<p>3. Press the <strong>Advanced Sharing</strong> button from the folder properties window and select <strong>Share this folder</strong> checkbox.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-81" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/advanced-sharing.jpg" alt="Advanced Sharing" width="367" height="370" /></p>\r\n<p>4. Press the <strong>Permissions</strong> button and manage the access you want to establish for other users.<br /> For example, if you want to give full control for a folder check the <strong>Full Control</strong> option in the <strong>Allow</strong> column and then users will be able not only to watch and download files from the folder but also to copy their files to it and change/delete files in the folder you are sharing.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-82" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-permissions.jpg" alt="Sharing Permissions" width="377" height="456" /></p>\r\n<p>5. Additionally it is necessary to check <strong>Advanced sharing settings</strong>:</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">5.1. Go to <strong>Control Panel -&gt; Network and Sharing Center</strong>.<br /> 5.2. Select in the left pane <strong>Advanced sharing settings</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-334 size-full" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-network-control.jpg" alt="Network Control Left Pane" width="216" height="223" /></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">5.3. Set these options under the <strong>Public</strong> section:</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;"><em>- Turn on network discovery</em><br /> <em>- Turn on file and print sharing</em><br /> <em>- Turn on sharing so anyone with network access can read and write files in the Public folders</em><br /> <em>- Turn off password protected sharing</em></p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-335" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-advanced-options.jpg" alt="Sharing Advanced Options" width="634" height="735" /></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">5.4. Save changes.</p>\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Windows XP</span></h3>\r\n<p>For the XP system I use my own example. I needed to share my Documents folder only for reading and the share folder inside it for reading and writing. It was accomplished this way.</p>\r\n<p>1. Go to <strong>Tools -&gt; Folder Options</strong> menu.</p>\r\n<p>2. Go to <strong>View</strong> tab.</p>\r\n<p>3. Uncheck <strong>Use simple file sharing</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>4. OK.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-398" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-xp-folder-options.jpg" alt="Sharing XP folder options" width="386" height="474" /></p>\r\n<p>5. Open <strong>Documents</strong> folder<strong> Properties</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>6. Go to <strong>Sharing</strong> tab and select <strong>Share this folder</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-403" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-xp-documents-properties.jpg" alt="Sharing XP Documents properties" width="367" height="480" /></p>\r\n<p>7. Press <strong>Permissions</strong> and set <strong>Full Control</strong> for <strong>Everyone</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-402" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-xp-documents-permissions.jpg" alt="Sharing XP Documents permissions" width="367" height="449" /></p>\r\n<p>8. OK.</p>\r\n<p>9. Go to <strong>Security</strong> tab, select <strong>Everyone</strong> as group.</p>\r\n<p>10. Uncheck <strong>Write</strong> checkbox in the <strong>Permissions</strong> <strong>Allow</strong> column (<em>Full Control</em> and <em>Modify</em> will uncheck automatically).</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-401" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-xp-documents-security.jpg" alt="Sharing XP Documents security" width="367" height="480" /></p>\r\n<p>11. Open the <strong>Documents</strong> folder and open <strong>Properties</strong> of the <strong>share</strong> folder inside it.</p>\r\n<p>12. Set <strong>Share</strong> this folder and press <strong>Permissions</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>13. Set <strong>Full Control</strong> for <strong>Everyone</strong>. OK.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-400" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-xp-share-folder-permissions.jpg" alt="Sharing XP share folder permissions" width="367" height="449" /></p>\r\n<p>14. Go to <strong>Security</strong> tab and set <strong>Full Control</strong> for <strong>Everyone</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-399" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-xp-share-folder-security.jpg" alt="Sharing XP share folder security" width="367" height="480" /></p>\r\n<p>15. OK.</p>\r\n<p>16. Now it\'s possible to view and copy files from the <strong>Documents</strong> folder and its subfolder. And <strong>share</strong> folder allows to write files to it and change existing ones.</p>', 'Manage Sharing Permissions', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'manage-sharing-permissions', '', '', '2015-03-25 13:14:24', '2015-03-25 13:14:24', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=80', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(86, 1, '2015-03-02 21:20:49', '2015-03-02 18:20:49', '<p>1. Go to <strong>Control Panel</strong> -> <strong>Network and Sharing Center</strong> -> <strong>Change adapter settings</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-87" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/control-panel-network.jpg" alt="Control Panel Network" width="266" height="596" /></p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-92" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/network-folder-sidebar.jpg" alt="Network Folder Sidebar" width="197" height="171" /></p>\r\n<p>2. Rightclick the <strong>Local Area Connection</strong> and select <strong>Properties</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/lac-properties.jpg" alt="Local Area Connection Properties" width="377" height="474" /></p>\r\n<p>3. On the <strong>Networking</strong> tab doubleclick the <strong>Internet Protocol Version 4</strong> item to open its properties.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-89" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ipv4-properties.jpg" alt="IPv4 Properties" width="414" height="461" /></p>\r\n<p>4. If you have the access to Internet through this connection and you get your IP address automatically (you have the "Obtain an IP address automatically" radio button on) then go to the <strong>Alternate Configuration</strong> tab.<br /> If you just want to establish home network connection for this Local Area Connection element then select the <strong>General</strong> tab.</p>\r\n<p>5. Select the <strong>User configured</strong> option on the <strong>Alternate Configuration</strong> tab and type this information:<br /> IP address - 192.168.1.1<br /> Subnet Mask - 255.255.255.0<br /> Approve all changes</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-88" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ipv4-alternate.jpg" alt="IPv4 Alternate Configuration" width="414" height="461" /></p>\r\n<p>6. Go to other computers and <strong>repeat</strong> all steps. For the IP address field change last digit as the IP wshould be unqique for each computer in the network.</p>\r\n<p>7. Check that all computers have the same <strong>Workgroup</strong>:</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">7.1. Press <strong>Win+Pause</strong> to open <strong>System properties</strong>.<br /> 7.2. Under the <strong>Computer name, domain, and workgroup settings</strong> check the <strong>Workgroup</strong> option.<br /> 7.3. To change the workgroup name press <strong>Change settings</strong> on the right then the <strong>Change</strong> button and type the name in the <strong>Workgroup</strong> field.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-102" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/system-properties-workgroup.jpg" alt="System Properties Workgroup" width="656" height="119" /></p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-103" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/workgroup-edit.jpg" alt="Workgroup Edit" width="763" height="477" /></p>\r\n<p>8. Connect computers and check the connection:</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">8.1. Press Win+R, type "cmd".<br /> 8.2. Type "<strong>ping 192.168.1.2</strong>" or "<strong>ping [other-computer-name]</strong>" from the computer with the IP 192.168.1.1.<br /> 8.3. All the Packets should be received.<br /> 8.4. Also press Win+R and type "<strong>\\\\192.168.1.2</strong>" or "<strong>\\\\[other-computer-name]</strong>".<br /> 8.5. This should open the remote computer sharing folders list.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-93" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ping-home-network.jpg" alt="Ping Home Network" width="677" height="342" /></p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-95" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-run-pc-name.jpg" alt="Open Sharing Folder From Run Window By PC Name" width="427" height="235" /></p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-94" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/remote-pc-sharing.jpg" alt="Remote PC Sharing Folder" width="703" height="221" /></p>\r\n', 'Set Up a Home Network', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'set-up-a-home-network', '', '', '2015-03-27 18:12:23', '2015-03-27 18:12:23', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=86', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(96, 1, '2015-03-02 21:15:53', '2015-03-02 18:15:53', '<h3>I. Working with Registry</h3>\r\n<p>It is possible to remove the following left <strong>Navigation Pane</strong> elements through the <strong>Registry</strong>:</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Favorites<br /> Libraries<br /> Homegroup<br /> Computer<br /> Network</p>\r\n<p>For any item use these steps:</p>\r\n<p>1. Win+R -&gt; "regedit"</p>\r\n<p>2. Go to the appropriate branch in</p>\r\n<pre>HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\\CLSID\\[ID]\\ShellFolder</pre>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-98" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/remove-pane-items-registry.jpg" alt="Remove Pane Items Registry" width="719" height="228" /></p>\r\n<p>3. Change the <strong>Attributes</strong> key value to [v1] to <strong>remove</strong> or [v2] to <strong>restore</strong> the appropriate item.</p>\r\n<p>4. <strong>Log Off</strong> or <strong>Restart</strong> the system.</p>\r\n<p>The [ID], [v1], [v2] parts are following:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Favorites</strong><br /> {323CA680-C24D-4099-B94D-446DD2D7249E}<br /> a9400100<br /> a0900100</p>\r\n<p><strong>Libraries</strong><br /> {031E4825-7B94-4dc3-B131-E946B44C8DD5}<br /> b090010d<br /> b080010d</p>\r\n<p><strong>Homegroup</strong><br /> {B4FB3F98-C1EA-428d-A78A-D1F5659CBA93}<br /> b094010c<br /> b084010c</p>\r\n<p><strong>Computer</strong><br /> {20D04FE0-3AEA-1069-A2D8-08002B30309D}<br /> b094010c<br /> Remove the Attributes key</p>\r\n<p><strong>Network</strong><br /> {F02C1A0D-BE21-4350-88B0-7367FC96EF3C}<br /> b0940064<br /> b0040064</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-97" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/left-pane-after-removal.jpg" alt="Left Pane After Removal" width="233" height="365" /></p>\r\n<h3>II. Using the program</h3>\r\n<p>1. Download the <a href="http://www.door2windows.com/windows-7-navigation-pane-customizer-show-hide-rename-items-in-windows-explorer-navigation-pane/" target="_blank"><strong>Windows 7 Navigation Pane Customizer</strong></a> program</p>\r\n<p>2. Open it and uncheck unnecessary items.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-413" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/remove-left-pane-program.jpg" alt="Remove left pane program" width="346" height="215" /></p>', 'Remove Items from the Left Navigation Pane', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'remove-items-from-the-left-navigation-pane', '', '', '2015-03-26 14:05:28', '2015-03-26 14:05:28', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=96', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(105, 1, '2015-03-03 16:26:19', '2015-03-03 13:26:19', '<p>1. To select a <strong>link text</strong> hold the <strong>Alt</strong> key and select it.</p>\r\n<p>2. To open <strong>search</strong> results in a <strong>new tab</strong> press <strong>Alt+Enter</strong> in the search bar.</p>\r\n<p>3. To open <strong>new tab</strong> from the <strong>Run window</strong> or <strong>Command Line</strong> for a custom profile:</p>\r\n<pre>firefox -p [prof-name] -new-tab http://google.com</pre>\r\n<p>4. If you are closing a tab by mouse wheel and get a dialog <strong>"This page is asking you to confirm that you want to leave"</strong> then press the wheel again to close the tab completely.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-391" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ff-confirm-leave-page.jpg" alt="Firefox Confirm Leave Page" width="578" height="142" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Browser Tricks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'browser-tricks', '', '', '2015-03-25 07:29:48', '2015-03-25 07:29:48', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=105', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(107, 1, '2015-03-03 15:48:08', '2015-03-03 12:48:08', '1. Type <strong>\'about:config\'</strong> in the address bar.\r\n\r\n2. Create or edit the <strong>general.useragent.override</strong> preference.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-108" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/add-user-agent-pref.jpg" alt="Add User Agent Pref" width="325" height="143" />\r\n\r\n3. Set one of these values for appropriate <strong>user agent</strong>:\r\n\r\n<strong>Desktop Firefox</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:36.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/36.0"</pre>\r\n<strong>Android (Phone)</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 4.4.2; Nexus 5 Build/KOT49H) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/33.0.1750.166 Mobile Safari/537.36"</pre>\r\n<strong>Android (Tablet)</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 4.4.2; Nexus 7 Build/KOT49H) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/34.0.1847.114 Safari/537.36"</pre>\r\n<strong>iPhone</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; CPU iPhone OS 7_1_1 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/537.51.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/7.0 Mobile/11D201 Safari/9537.53"</pre>\r\n<strong>iPad</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (iPad; CPU OS 8_1_1 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/600.1.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0 Mobile/12B436"</pre>\r\n<strong>Microsoft IE</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 9.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/5.0)"</pre>\r\n<strong>Chrome</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/37.0.2049.0 Safari/537.36"</pre>\r\n<strong>Firefox OS</strong>\r\n<pre>"Mozilla/5.0 (Mobile; rv:26.0) Gecko/26.0 Firefox/26.0"</pre>\r\n<strong>Lynx</strong>\r\n<pre>"Lynx/2.8.5rel.1 libwww-FM/2.14 SSL-MM/1.4.1 GNUTLS/1.0.16"</pre>\r\n<a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/override-pref.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-275 size-full" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/override-pref-crop.jpg" alt="override-pref-crop" width="895" height="60" /></a>\r\n\r\n4. To restore default user agent assign the empty string to the preference or rightclick on it and press <strong>Reset</strong>.', 'Change User Agent', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'change-user-agent', '', '', '2015-03-23 21:29:54', '2015-03-23 21:29:54', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=107', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(110, 1, '2015-03-03 15:53:19', '2015-03-03 12:53:19', '<h4>1. Performance</h4>\nDisable the session restore on crash\n<pre>browser.sessionstore.resume_from_crash -&gt; false</pre>\nReduce memory usage by reducing images store time in the memory\n<pre>image.mem.min_discard_timeout_ms -&gt; &lt; 10000</pre>\nImages cache maximum capacity\n<pre>browser.cache.memory.capacity -&gt; ~5000 (KB)</pre>\nMax pages to store in memory for Back/Forward buttons\n<pre>browser.sessionhistory.max_total_viewers -&gt; 3</pre>\nDisable/enable image loading\n<pre>permissions.default.image -&gt; [0]: always; [1]: never; [2]: don\'t load third party images</pre>\n<h4>2. Interface</h4>\nTurn off the “Downloads Complete” alert\n<pre>browser.download.manager.showAlertOnComplete -&gt; false</pre>\nClose multiple tabs without warning\n<pre>browser.tabs.warnOnCloseOtherTabs -&gt; false</pre>\nShow separate Downloads window [F29+]\n<pre>browser.download.useToolkitUI</pre>\nIf not working use the Downloads Window extension\n\nClassic search bar [F29+]\n<pre>browser.search.showOneOffButtons -&gt; false</pre>\nDisable tabs animation on open/close [F29+]\n<pre>browser.tabs.animate -&gt; false</pre>\nDisable Close button in tab\n<pre>browser.tabs.closebuttons -&gt; false</pre>\nFor Firefox 29+ use "No Close Buttons" extension\n<h4>3. Selection</h4>\nChange selection background color in hex format (#000000, #a1cef2)\n\nNormal text background\n<pre>ui.textSelectBackground</pre>\nFound text background\n<pre>ui.textSelectBackgroundAttention</pre>\nInactive window found text background\n<pre>ui.textSelectBackgroundDisabled</pre>\nText color\n<pre>ui.textSelectForeground</pre>\nOther colors\n<pre>ui.textBackground</pre>\n<pre>ui.textForeground</pre>\n<pre>ui.textHighlightBackground</pre>\n<pre>ui.textHighlightForeground</pre>\n<h4>3. Miscellaneous</h4>\nDisable addons install delay\n<pre>security.dialog_enable_delay -&gt; 0</pre>', 'Tweaks for \'about:config\'', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tweaks-for-aboutconfig', '', '', '2015-03-03 15:53:19', '2015-03-03 12:53:19', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=110', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(111, 1, '2015-03-03 16:26:17', '2015-03-03 13:26:17', '1. Win+R -&gt; <strong>"firefox -p -no-remote" </strong>to open <strong>Firefox Profile Manager</strong>.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-114" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/profiles.jpg" alt="Firefox Profiles" width="336" height="255" />\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n2. Press <strong>Create Profile</strong>.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-112" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/create-profile.jpg" alt="Create Profile" width="501" height="382" />\r\n\r\n3. Type a new profile name.\r\n\r\n4. Finish, Exit.\r\n\r\n5. Copy Firefox <strong>icon</strong> (Ctrl+C, Ctrl+V).\r\n\r\n6. Open the new <strong>icon Properties</strong>.\r\n\r\n7. In the <strong>Target</strong> field add this string to the end:\r\n<pre>-p [your-created-profile-name] -no-remote</pre>\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-113" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/firefox-shortcut.jpg" alt="Firefox Shortcut Properties" width="367" height="507" />\r\n8. OK.', 'Run Multiple Instances', '1. Win+R -> <strong>“firefox -p -no-remote”</strong> to open Firefox Profile Manager.\r\n2. Press Create Profile.\r\n3. Type a new profile name.\r\n4. Finish, Exit.\r\n5. Copy Firefox icon (Ctrl+C, Ctrl+V).\r\n6. Open the new icon Properties.\r\n7. In the Target field add this string to the end.\r\n<pre>-p [your-created-profile-name] -no-remote</pre>', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'run-multiple-instances', '', '', '2015-03-24 10:56:31', '2015-03-24 10:56:31', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=111', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(115, 1, '2015-03-03 16:26:16', '2015-03-03 16:26:16', '<h3>1. Tools</h3>\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-133 size-full" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/adblock1.png" alt="adblock1" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Adblock Plus" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/adblock-plus/" target="_blank"><strong>Adblock Plus</strong></a> - Blocks advertisements.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-134 size-full" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/noscript1.png" alt="noscript1" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="NoScript" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/noscript/" target="_blank"><strong>NoScript</strong></a> - Allows JavaScript, Java and other executable content to run only from trusted domains.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-131" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/xnotifier1.png" alt="xnotifier1" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="X-notifier" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/xnotifier/" target="_blank"><strong>X-notifier</strong></a> - Notifier for gmail, yahoo, hotmail, aol webmails.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-123" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="imacros1" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="imacros" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/imacros-for-firefox/" target="_blank"><strong>iMacros</strong></a> - Automate Firefox. Record and replay repetitious work.\r\n<h3>2. Interface</h3>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-128" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sidebar-retainer.png" alt="sidebar-retainer" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Bookmarks Sidebar Scroll Retainer" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/bm-sidebar-scroll-retainer/" target="_blank"><strong>Bookmarks Sidebar Scroll Retainer</strong></a> - Memorizes Bookmarks/History sidebar\'s vertical scroll position.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-117" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="add-to-search" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Add to Search Bar" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/add-to-search-bar/" target="_blank"><strong>Add to Search Bar</strong></a> - Make any pages\' search functionality available in the Search Bar.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-127" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="searchwp" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="SearchWP" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/searchwp/" target="_blank"><strong>SearchWP</strong></a> - Search multiple words. Jump-to-word buttons and highlighting for the search box content\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-137" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="extensionGeneric" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<strong><a title="UrlbarExt" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/urlbarext/" target="_blank">UrlbarExt</a></strong> - Extends the Location Bar with set of commands (Shorten URL, Copy URL, Search site, Go up, pNg, Tag pages easily, Navigate through sequential URLs, View page cached version, Surf anonymously using online servers, Twitter)\r\n\r\n<strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-137" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="extensionGeneric" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Downloads Window" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/downloads-window/" target="_blank">Downloads Window</a></strong> - Separate Downloads window.\r\n<div></div>\r\n<h3>3. Web Development</h3>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-121" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="firebug" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Firebug" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/firebug/" target="_blank"><strong>Firebug</strong></a> - Web Development toolbox.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-129" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="webdev" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Web Developer" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/web-developer/" target="_blank"><strong>Web Developer</strong></a> - The Toolbar with useful web tools.\r\n\r\n<strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-137" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="extensionGeneric" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="DOM Inspector" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/dom-inspector-6622/" target="_blank">DOM Inspector</a></strong> - Inspects the structure and properties of a window and its contents.\r\n\r\n<strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-137" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="extensionGeneric" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Element Inspector" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/dom-inspector-6622/" target="_blank">Element Inspector</a></strong> - In the DOM Inspector addon quickly navigates to elements by Shift+Rightclicking on it.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-120" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="colorzilla" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="ColorZilla" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/element-inspector/" target="_blank"><strong>ColorZilla</strong></a> - Color picker.\r\n\r\n<strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-137" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="extensionGeneric" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Firesizer" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/firesizer/" target="_blank">Firesizer</a></strong> - Show window size in the addon bar on resizing. Set custom window size. Needs The Addon Bar addon.\r\n<div></div>\r\n<h3>4. Miscellaneous</h3>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-132" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/youtube.png" alt="youtube" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Easy YouTube Video Downloader" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/easy-youtube-video-download/" target="_blank"><strong>Easy YouTube Video Downloader</strong></a> - Download YouTube videos.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-119" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addon-default-icon-64.png" alt="aniweather" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="Aniweather" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/aniweather/" target="_blank"><strong>Aniweather</strong></a> - Animated Weather.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-118" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/addonbar.png" alt="addonbar" width="64" height="48" />\r\n<a title="The Addon Bar" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/the-addon-bar/" target="_blank"><strong>The Addon Bar</strong></a> - restores the bar for F29+.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-124" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/noclose.png" alt="noclose" width="64" height="64" />\r\n<a title="No Close Buttons" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/no-close-buttons/" target="_blank"><strong>No Close Buttons</strong></a> - Remove the Close buttons from the tabs.', 'Useful Addons', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'useful-addons', '', '', '2015-04-04 06:12:24', '2015-04-04 06:12:24', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=115', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(145, 1, '2015-03-03 19:38:29', '2015-03-03 16:38:29', '<p>1. Add a line</p>\r\n<pre>Ctl+Alt+Up/Down\r\ncommand: select_lines\r\nargs: forward [up:false, down:true]</pre>\r\n<p>2. Split selection into lines</p>\r\n<pre>Ctrl+Shift+L for a selected block\r\ncommand: split_selection_into_lines</pre>\r\n<p>3. Add next occurrence</p>\r\n<pre>Ctrl+D\r\ncommand: find_under_expand</pre>\r\n<p>4. Find all occurrences</p>\r\n<pre>Alt+F3\r\ncommand: find_all_under</pre>\r\n<p>5. Undo add line/occurrence</p>\r\n<pre>Ctrl+U\r\ncommand: soft_undo</pre>\r\n<p>6. Add with mouse</p>\r\n<pre>Ctrl+Mouse click\r\nsource: Default.sublime-mousemap</pre>\r\n<p>7. Add/Remove custom blocks to selection</p>\r\n<pre>Ctrl+DragSelect - add to selection\r\nAlt+DragSelect - remove from selection\r\nsource: Default.sublime-mousemap</pre>\r\n<p>8. Create/Add/Remove selection by columns</p>\r\n<pre>Shift+MouseRight+DragSelect - create selection\r\nCtrl+Shift+MouseRight+DragSelect - add to selection\r\nAlt+Shift+MouseRight+DragSelect - remove from selection\r\n\r\n[Ctrl|Alt]+MouseWheel+DragSelect - the same actions\r\n\r\nsource: Default.sublime-mousemap</pre>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Multiple Selection', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'multiple-selection', '', '', '2015-03-25 06:31:10', '2015-03-25 06:31:10', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=145', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(146, 1, '2015-03-03 19:39:49', '2015-03-03 16:39:49', '<p>To add a shortcut to end a line with separators [: ; , .] use these steps:</p>\r\n<p>1. Tools -&gt; Record Macro (<strong>Ctrl+Q</strong>).</p>\r\n<p>2. Press <strong>End</strong> in a line and type a <strong>separator</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>3. Tools -&gt; Stop Recording Macro (Ctrl+Q).</p>\r\n<p>4. Tools -&gt; Save Macro.</p>\r\n<p>5. Preferences  -&gt; Key Bindings -&gt; User.</p>\r\n<p>6. Add the line</p>\r\n<pre>{"keys": ["&lt;shortcut&gt;"], "command": "run_macro_file", "args": {"file": "Packages/User/&lt;macro-name&gt;.sublime-macro"}}</pre>\r\n<h3>End line with semicolon macro (<em>end-semicolon.sublime-macro)</em></h3>\r\n<pre>[\r\n  {\r\n    "args":\r\n    {\r\n      "extend": false,\r\n      "to": "eol"\r\n    },\r\n    "command": "move_to"\r\n  },\r\n  {\r\n    "args":\r\n    {\r\n      "characters": ";"\r\n    },\r\n    "command": "insert"\r\n  }\r\n]</pre>\r\n<h3>The keyboard shortcut</h3>\r\n<pre>{"keys": ["ctrl+;"], "command": "run_macro_file", "args": {"file": "Packages/User/end-semicolon.sublime-macro"}},</pre>', 'End a Line with Separators', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'end-a-line-with-separators', '', '', '2015-03-29 14:45:46', '2015-03-29 14:45:46', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=146', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(147, 1, '2015-03-03 19:41:13', '2015-03-03 16:41:13', '1. Go to <strong>Packages/Color Scheme - Default</strong>.\n\n2. Open the file <strong>[theme-name].tmTheme</strong>.\n\n3. Find the syntax element among the <strong>&lt;key&gt;</strong> tags.\n\n4. Change the color in the <strong>&lt;string&gt;</strong> tag.\n\n5. Examples:\n\n<strong>lineHighlight</strong> - set current line background in the next <strong>&lt;string&gt;</strong> attribute\n<strong>Function name</strong> - set function name foreground in programming languages (JavaScript, PHP, Java) in the <strong>&lt;string&gt;</strong> tag under the <strong>"foreground" &lt;key&gt;</strong> tag.\n<strong>Comment</strong> - comments color, the same <strong>&lt;string&gt;</strong> under <strong>"foreground" &lt;key&gt;</strong>.', 'Change Syntax Colors', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'change-syntax-colors', '', '', '2015-03-03 19:41:13', '2015-03-03 16:41:13', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=147', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(148, 1, '2015-03-03 19:44:14', '2015-03-03 16:44:14', 'If you have a file with an extension unknown to Sublime Text it is possible to add this extension to any syntax patterns which the editor has by default.\n\n1. Go to View -&gt; Syntax -&gt; <strong>Open all with current extension as...</strong>\n<strong>OR</strong> in the right down corner press Plain Text -&gt; <strong>Open all with current extension as...</strong>\n\n2. Also you may create a settings file to include the extension.\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">2.1. Go to Packages/<strong>User</strong> folder.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">2.2. Create a file <strong>[ext].sublime-settings</strong>, where [ext] - is one of the predefined extensions (js, html, css, ini).</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">2.3. Put this contents:</p>\n\n<pre style="padding-left: 30px;">{\n  "extensions":\n  [\n    "[new-ext]"\n  ]\n}</pre>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">where [new-ext] - is your new extension without dot.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">2.4. <strong>Restart</strong> Subilme Text.</p>\n<strong>Example</strong>:\nYou have a file <strong>test.abc</strong> and want it to have <strong>JavaScript</strong> syntax.\nCreate a file <strong>JavaScript.sublime-settings</strong> and put\n<pre style="padding-left: 30px;">{\n  "extensions":\n  [\n    "abc"\n  ]\n}</pre>', 'Add Extension to Predefined Syntax', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'add-extension-to-predefined-syntax', '', '', '2015-03-03 19:44:14', '2015-03-03 16:44:14', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=148', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(149, 1, '2015-03-03 19:47:26', '2015-03-03 19:47:26', '<a title="SideBarEnhancements" href="https://github.com/titoBouzout/SideBarEnhancements" target="_blank"><strong>SideBarEnhancements</strong></a>\n\nProvides enhancements to the operations on the Sidebar.\n<em>New File</em> - enter filename immediately\n<em>Open/Run</em>\n<em>Open in Browser/New Window</em>\n<em>Open With</em>\n<em>Reveal </em>- open folder in Windows Explorer\n\n<!--more-->\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-155" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sidebar-enhancements.jpg" alt="Sidebar Enhancements" width="291" height="560" />\n\n<a title="Duplicate Lines" href="https://github.com/wjthomas9/duplicate-lines" target="_blank"><strong>Duplicate Lines</strong></a>\n\nDuplicate multiple lines of text without worrying about the position of the cursor.\n\n<a title="Emmet" href="https://github.com/sergeche/emmet-sublime" target="_blank"><strong>Emmet</strong></a>\n\nHTML &amp; CSS toolkit\n\n<a title="INI file Syntax Highlighting" href="https://github.com/clintberry/sublime-text-2-ini" target="_blank"><strong>INI file Syntax Highlighting</strong></a>\n\n<a title="Package Control" href="https://packagecontrol.io/Package%20Control.sublime-package" target="_blank"><strong>Package Control</strong></a>\n\nInstall, remove, manage packages.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Useful Packages', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'useful-packages', '', '', '2015-04-04 06:12:36', '2015-04-04 06:12:36', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=149', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1075, 1, '2016-05-19 16:38:45', '2016-05-19 16:38:45', 'To create shortcuts for these Windows functions follow the next steps:\n\n1. From the <strong>Context menu</strong> on the Desktop or in any folder select <strong>New -&gt; Shortcut.</strong>\n\n2. In the Location field type:\n<ul>\n	<li>For <strong>Shutdown:</strong>\n<code>shutdown.exe -s -t 00</code></li>\n	<li>For <strong>Restart</strong>\n<code>shutdown.exe -r -t 00</code></li>\n	<li>For <strong>Workstation lock</strong>\n<code>Rundll32.exe User32.dll,LockWorkStation</code></li>\n	<li>For <strong>Sleep</strong>\n<code>rundll32.exe powrprof.dll,SetSuspendState Sleep</code></li>\n	<li>For <strong>Hibernation</strong>\n<code>rundll32.exe powrprof.dll,SetSuspendState</code></li>\n</ul>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/create-shortcut.jpg" alt="Create Shortcut" width="447" height="327" />\n\n3. Press Next and type the shortcut name.\n\n4. After it you can use the shortcut by <strong>doubleclicking</strong> on it or by assigning a <strong>keyboard shortcut</strong> to it (that can be done in its Properties <strong>Shortcut key</strong> field).\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-61" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/shortcut-properties.jpg" alt="Shortcut Properties" width="376" height="525" />', 'Shutdown, Restart, Lock, Sleep and Hibernate Shortcuts', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-05-19 16:38:45', '2016-05-19 16:38:45', '', 5, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/blog/5-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
