(342, 1, '2015-03-24 20:50:42', '2015-03-24 20:50:42', '<p><span style="font-size:1.1em">I. <strong>Win+R</strong> -&gt;<strong> "%windir%"</strong> or go to <strong>C:\\Windows</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size:1.1em">II. Put a <strong>shortcut</strong> to the program in this folder.</span></p>\r\n<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\r\n<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Get existing shortcut from other place</span>:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Copy shortcut from <strong>Desktop</strong> or <strong>Start Menu</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Rename it to a short name.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Create new shortcut from the program folder</span>:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to the program folder in another window.</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Put program icon to the Windows folder.</p>\r\n<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\r\n<li><strong>Drag\'n\'drop</strong> program icon:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Drag the program icon to the <strong>Task Bar</strong> label of the opened <strong>Windows</strong> folder until that folder appears.</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Holding the <strong>Alt key</strong> release the dragging somewhere on the white space.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-345" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/custom-run-create-shotcut-by-drag.jpg" alt="Custom Run Command Create Shortcut By Drag" width="463" height="232" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Copy/paste</strong> as shortcut:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press <strong>Ctrl+C</strong> on a program icon in <strong>Windows Explorer</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Go to the <strong>Windows</strong> folder or maybe <strong>Desktop</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>From the <strong>Context</strong> menu select <strong>Paste Shortcut</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-415" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/custom-run-paste-as-shortcut.jpg" alt="Custom run paste as shortcut" width="271" height="78" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Copy (if needed) the pasted shortcut to the Windows folder.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Rename it to a short name.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Create new shortcut in place</span>:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In the <strong>Windows</strong> folder select <strong>New -&gt; Shortcut</strong> from the context menu.</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Select location of a program or another link.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-346" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/custom-run-create-shotcut-in-place.jpg" alt="Custom Run Command Create Shortcut In Place" width="628" height="459" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Enter a short name.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-347" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/custom-run-create-shotcut-in-place-short-name.jpg" alt="Custom Run Command Create Shortcut In Place Set Name" width="628" height="459" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Finish.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style="font-size:1.1em">III. <strong>Win+R</strong> -&gt;<strong> [short-name]</strong> opens the program.</span></p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-344" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/custom-run-command-check.jpg" alt="Custom Run Check New Command" width="427" height="236" /></p>', 'Create Custom Run Commands', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'create-custom-run-commands', '', '', '2015-03-26 14:22:46', '2015-03-26 14:22:46', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=342', 0, 'post', '', 0),
