(365, 1, '2015-03-24 21:26:19', '2015-03-24 21:26:19', '<p>1. <strong>Win+R -&gt; "regedit"</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>2. Adjust the following branches and keys:</p>\r\n<pre>[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Control Panel\\Desktop]\r\n"AutoEndTasks"="1"\r\n"HungAppTimeout"="0"\r\n"WaitToKillAppTimeout"="1000"\r\n\r\n[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control]\r\n"WaitToKillServiceTimeout"="1000"\r\n\r\n[HKEY_USERS\\.DEFAULT\\Control Panel\\Desktop]\r\n"AutoEndTasks"="1"\r\n"HungAppTimeout"="0"\r\n"WaitToKillAppTimeout"="1000"</pre>\r\n<p>If there is no some settings create them as <strong>String</strong> from <strong>Context menu -&gt; New -&gt; String Value</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-366" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/faster-shutdown-reg.jpg" alt="Registry Keys For Faster Shutdown" width="586" height="313" /></p>\r\n<p>3. Or create a<strong> .reg</strong> file, just add :</p>\r\n<pre>Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00</pre>\r\n<p>to the top and two blank lines after that line and one blank line in the end.<br />The .reg file can be run to add those settings to the registry.</p>\r\n<p>4. Now if any program is opened and running on the shutdown it should close automatically without saving changed data.</p>', 'Faster Shutdown and Autoend Hung Programs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'faster-shutdown-and-autoend-hung-programs', '', '', '2015-03-24 21:26:19', '2015-03-24 21:26:19', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=365', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(366, 1, '2015-03-24 21:25:04', '2015-03-24 21:25:04', '', 'Registry Keys For Faster Shutdown', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'faster-shutdown-reg', '', '', '2015-03-24 21:25:26', '2015-03-24 21:25:26', '', 365, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/faster-shutdown-reg.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(369, 1, '2015-03-24 21:37:44', '2015-03-24 21:37:44', '<h3>1. To change default Program Files directory:</h3>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n<li>Go to the <strong>registry</strong></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Find the branch</p>\r\n<pre>HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion</pre>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Change the <strong>ProgramFilesDir</strong> key to a <strong>new path</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>2. Disable balloon messages in the tray</h3>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n<li>Go to the <strong>registry</strong></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Find the branch</p>\r\n<pre>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\Advanced</pre>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Set/create DWORD key <strong>EnableBalloonTips=0</strong></li>\r\n<li>Logoff/Restart</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>3. Assign keyboard shortcut to a Desktop/Start Menu shortcut</h3>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n<li>From the context menu of a shortcut open its <strong>Properties</strong></li>\r\n<li>In the <strong>Shortcut Key</strong> field type new shortcut</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-371" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/shortcut-key-shortcut.jpg" alt="Shortcut Properties Shortcut Key" width="437" height="589" /></p>\r\n<h3>4. Remove "Shortcut" text from new created shortcuts</h3>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n<li>Go to the <strong>registry</strong></li>\r\n<li><p>Find the branch</p><pre>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer</pre></li>\r\n<li>Set/create Binary key <strong>link="00 00 00 00"</strong></li>\r\n<li>Logoff/Restart</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-370" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/remove-shortcut-text-reg.jpg" alt="Remove shortcut text registry key" width="527" height="524" /> </p>', 'Some Minor Advices', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'some-minor-advices', '', '', '2015-03-24 21:37:44', '2015-03-24 21:37:44', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=369', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(370, 1, '2015-03-24 21:29:15', '2015-03-24 21:29:15', '', 'Remove shortcut text registry key', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'remove-shortcut-text-reg', '', '', '2015-03-24 21:29:49', '2015-03-24 21:29:49', '', 369, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/remove-shortcut-text-reg.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(371, 1, '2015-03-24 21:29:23', '2015-03-24 21:29:23', '', 'Shortcut Properties Shortcut Key', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'shortcut-key-shortcut', '', '', '2015-03-24 21:30:16', '2015-03-24 21:30:16', '', 369, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/shortcut-key-shortcut.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(379, 1, '2015-03-25 06:47:19', '2015-03-25 06:47:19', '<p>1. <strong>Ctrl+F3</strong> - find next word under cursor</p>\r\n<pre><strong>command:</strong> find_under</pre>\r\n<p>2. <strong>Alt+Left/Right</strong> - move cursor by subwords<br /><strong>Alt+Shift+Left/Right</strong> - select subwords</p>\r\n<pre><strong>command:</strong> move\r\n<strong>args:</strong> {"by": "subwords", "forward": false/true}\r\n<strong>args:</strong> {"by": "subwords", "forward": false/true, "extend":true}</pre>\r\n<p><strong>example:</strong> word1_word2_word3<br />Moves/Extends word1/2/3 separately. With <strong>Ctrl</strong> works with all string.</p>\r\n<p>3. <strong>Ctrl+Shift+Backspace</strong> - delete all to the start of the line<br /><strong>Ctrl+Shift+Del</strong> - delete all to the end of the line</p>\r\n<pre><strong>command:</strong> run_macro_file\r\n<strong>args:</strong> {"file": "res://Packages/Default/Delete to Hard BOL.sublime-macro"}\r\n<strong>args:</strong> {"file": "res://Packages/Default/Delete to Hard EOL.sublime-macro"}</pre>\r\n<p>4. <strong>F12</strong> - go to function definition<br />For this a folder with sources must be in the project.</p>\r\n<p>5. <strong>Alt+.</strong> - close tag</p>\r\n<pre>command: close_tag</pre>\r\n<p>6. To go to a part, tag, class of an HTML page press <strong>Ctrl+P </strong>and type <strong>#</strong>. Then type a class or tagname.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-529" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/tricks-go-html.png" alt="Sublime Tricks go to HTML part" width="867" height="160" /></p>\r\n<p>7. <strong>Ctrl+G</strong> - go to line number.</p>\r\n<p>8. <strong>Ctrl+R</strong> - open function list.</p>\r\n<p>9. <strong>Ctrl+Shift+J</strong> - select text which is similarly indented.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-535" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/tricks-similar-indent.png" alt="Sublime Tricks similar indented text selection" width="511" height="521" /></p>\r\n<p>10. <strong>Ctrl+Shift+A</strong> - select all inside tag.</p>\r\n<pre>command: expand_selection\r\nargs: {"to": "tag"}</pre>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-537" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/tricks-select-inside-tag.png" alt="Sublime tricks select all inside tag" width="618" height="281" /></p>', 'Some Shortcuts and Tricks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'some-shortcuts-and-tricks', '', '', '2015-03-29 12:33:56', '2015-03-29 12:33:56', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=379', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(381, 1, '2015-03-25 06:55:34', '2015-03-25 06:55:34', '<h3>1. General selections</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><p>Hold <strong>Ctrl+LeftKey</strong> and select to <strong>add</strong> block to selection.</p><p>\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-384" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/mouse-actions-add-block.jpg" alt="Mouse Actions Add Block" width="604" height="342" /></p></li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>Alt+LeftKey</strong> and select to <strong>remove</strong> block from selection or reduce current selection.</li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>Shift</strong> and click/select outside of a selected block from both sides to<strong> add adjacent</strong> blocks.</li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>Alt+Shift</strong> and click before a block in a multiple selection to <strong>remove</strong> this block.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Doubleclick</strong> on a word, hold <strong>LeftKey</strong> and drag-select to select next <strong>full words</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>2. Selection by columns</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>Shift+RightKey</strong> and select to <strong>create</strong> multiple selection by columns.</li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>Ctrl+Shift+RightKey</strong> and select to <strong>add</strong> selection by columns to current multiple selection.</li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>Alt+Shift+RightKey</strong> and select to <strong>remove</strong> selection by columns from current multiple selection.</li>\r\n<li>The <strong>same selections</strong> by columns can be performed with the <strong>Wheel</strong> instead of <strong>Shift+RightKey</strong> combination.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>3. RightKey as modifier</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><p>Hold <strong>RightKey+LeftKey</strong> and select a block, then release to select <strong>whole lines</strong> in the start and end of selected block.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-385" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/mouse-actions-expand-to-line-end.jpg" alt="Mouse Actions Expand To Line End" width="586" height="204" /></p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-386" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/mouse-actions-expand-to-line-start.jpg" alt="Mouse Actions Expand To Line Start" width="586" height="204" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>RightKey</strong> and <strong>Doubleclick LeftKey</strong> to select a <strong>paragraph.</strong></li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>RightKey</strong> and <strong>Tripleclick LeftKey</strong> to select <strong>all.</strong></li>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>RightKey</strong> and turn <strong>Wheel</strong> to go to <strong>Next/Prev</strong> tab.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>4. Other actions</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Hold <strong>Ctrl</strong> and turn <strong>Wheel</strong> to go to change <strong>font size.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'Mouse Actions', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mouse-actions', '', '', '2015-03-25 06:55:34', '2015-03-25 06:55:34', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=381', 0, 'post', '', 0),
