(442, 1, '2015-03-28 18:46:50', '2015-03-28 18:46:50', '<article class="new-shortcuts">\r\n<h3>1. Working with windows</h3>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Up</span> – Maximize the current Window</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Down</span> – Restore down or minimize current Windows</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Left</span> – Dock the current Window to the left half of the screen</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Right</span> – Dock the current Window to the right half of the screen</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Home</span> – Minimize all but the current Window</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">Up</span> – Maximize vertical size</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">Down</span> – Restore vertical size</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">Left</span> – Jump to left monitor</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">Right</span> – Jump to right monitor</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Taskbar</h3>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Number</span> – Activate/Run the program with the Number</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Shift</span> + Number – Run new instance of the program with the Number</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">T</span> – Cycle through the buttons</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">T</span> – Cycle backwards</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">Click</span> or Wheel – Open a new instance</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">Rightclick</span> - Show classic context menu (works on Taskbar and Start Menu items)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Windows Explorer</h3>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Alt</span> + <span class="key">Up</span> – Go up a directory</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Alt</span> + <span class="key">P</span> – Toggle the preview panel</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Ctrl</span> + <span class="key">N</span> – Open a new Window</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Ctrl</span> + <span class="key">Scroll</span> – Change the view type (extra large, small, list view, detail, etc.)</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Ctrl</span> + <span class="key">E</span> - Select the search box</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Other shortcuts</h3>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> + <span class="key">X</span> – Mobility Center</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Ctrl</span> + <span class="key">Shift</span> + <span class="key">N</span> – Create new folder</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Login/Logout</h3>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Right</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Enter</span> – Shutdown</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Right</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Right</span> -&gt; <span class="key">R</span> – Restart</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Right</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Right</span> -&gt; <span class="key">S</span> – Sleep</p>\r\n<p class="shortcut-row"><span class="key">Win</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Right</span> -&gt; <span class="key">Right</span> -&gt; <span class="key">W</span> – Switch users</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Disable <strong>Win key</strong> shortcuts:</h3>\r\n<div>1. <strong>Win+R -&gt; "gpedit.msc"</strong>.</div>\r\n<div>2. Go to <strong>User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Windows Explorer</strong>.</div>\r\n<div>3. Doubleclick <strong>"Turn off Windows+X Hotkeys"</strong> in the right panel.</div>\r\n<div>4. Select <strong>Enable</strong>.</div>\r\n<div>5. OK.</div>\r\n</article>', 'New Keyboard Shortcuts', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-keyboard-shortcuts', '', '', '2015-04-04 06:06:04', '2015-04-04 06:06:04', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=442', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(454, 1, '2015-03-29 08:50:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p>1. Go to <strong>Control Panel</strong> -&gt; <strong>Network and Sharing Center</strong> -&gt; <strong>Change adapter settings</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-87" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/control-panel-network.jpg" alt="Control Panel Network" width="266" height="596" /></p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-92" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/network-folder-sidebar.jpg" alt="Network Folder Sidebar" width="197" height="171" /></p>\n<p>2. Rightclick the <strong>Local Area Connection</strong> and select <strong>Properties</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/lac-properties.jpg" alt="Local Area Connection Properties" width="377" height="474" /></p>\n<p>3. On the <strong>Networking</strong> tab doubleclick the <strong>Internet Protocol Version 4</strong> item to open its properties.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-89" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ipv4-properties.jpg" alt="IPv4 Properties" width="414" height="461" /></p>\n<p>4. If you have the access to Internet through this connection and you get your IP address automatically (you have the "Obtain an IP address automatically" radio button on) then go to the <strong>Alternate Configuration</strong> tab. <br /> If you just want to establish home network connection for this Local Area Connection element then select the <strong>General</strong> tab.</p>\n<p>5. Select the <strong>User configured</strong> option on the <strong>Alternate Configuration</strong> tab and type this information: <br /> IP address - 192.168.1.1 <br /> Subnet Mask - 255.255.255.0 <br /> Approve all changes</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-88" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ipv4-alternate.jpg" alt="IPv4 Alternate Configuration" width="414" height="461" /></p>\n<p>6. Go to other computers and <strong>repeat</strong> all steps. For the IP address field change last digit as the IP wshould be unqique for each computer in the network.</p>\n<p>7. Check that all computers have the same <strong>Workgroup</strong>:</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">7.1. Press <strong>Win+Pause</strong> to open <strong>System properties</strong>. <br /> 7.2. Under the <strong>Computer name, domain, and workgroup settings</strong> check the <strong>Workgroup</strong> option. <br /> 7.3. To change the workgroup name press <strong>Change settings</strong> on the right then the <strong>Change</strong> button and type the name in the <strong>Workgroup</strong> field.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-102" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/system-properties-workgroup.jpg" alt="System Properties Workgroup" width="656" height="119" /></p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-103" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/workgroup-edit.jpg" alt="Workgroup Edit" width="763" height="477" /></p>\n<p>8. Connect computers and check the connection:</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">8.1. Press Win+R, type "cmd". <br /> 8.2. Type "<strong>ping 192.168.1.2</strong>" or "<strong>ping [other-computer-name]</strong>" from the computer with the IP 192.168.1.1. <br /> 8.3. All the Packets should be received. <br /> 8.4. Also press Win+R and type "<strong>\\\\192.168.1.2</strong>" or "<strong>\\\\[other-computer-name]</strong>". <br /> 8.5. This should open the remote computer sharing folders list.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-93" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ping-home-network.jpg" alt="Ping Home Network" width="677" height="342" /></p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-95" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/sharing-run-pc-name.jpg" alt="Open Sharing Folder From Run Window By PC Name" width="427" height="235" /></p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-94" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/remote-pc-sharing.jpg" alt="Remote PC Sharing Folder" width="703" height="221" /></p>', 'Test2', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2015-03-29 08:50:12', '2015-03-29 08:50:12', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=454', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(462, 1, '2015-03-28 19:42:47', '2015-03-28 19:42:47', '1. <strong>Win+U</strong>\r\n\r\n2. Press <strong>Make the mouse easier to use</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-476" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/aero-off-utilman.jpg" alt="Aero off utilman" width="508" height="249" />\r\n\r\n3. Set <strong>Prevent windows from being automatically arranged when moved to the edged of the screen</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-475" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/aero-off-option1.jpg" alt="Aero Off Select option" width="589" height="87" />\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">====================== OR ======================</p>\r\n1. <strong>Win+R -&gt; "regedit"</strong>\r\n\r\n2. Go to branch\r\n<pre>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Control Panel\\Desktop</pre>\r\n3. Set value\r\n<pre>WindowArrangementActive=0</pre>\r\n4. Logoff/Restart', 'Turn Off Aero Snap', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'turn-off-aero-snap', '', '', '2015-03-28 19:42:47', '2015-03-28 19:42:47', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=462', 0, 'post', '', 0),
