(492, 1, '2015-03-28 21:08:17', '2015-03-28 21:08:17', '<h3>I. Through Command Line</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Win+R -&gt; "cmd"</strong></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Enter command</p>\r\n<pre>powercfg -h off</pre>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-497" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/disable-hiber-powercfg.jpg" alt="Disable hibernation pwercfg" width="677" height="343" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>II. Through Control Panel (system specific)</h3>\r\n<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\r\n<li>\r\n<h4>Windows XP</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to <strong>Control Panel -&gt; Power Options</strong> or <strong>Win+R -&gt; "powercfg.cpl"</strong></li>\r\n<li>Go to <strong>Hibernate</strong> tab</li>\r\n<li>Uncheck <strong>Enable hibernation</strong></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>OK</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-496" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/disable-hiber-power-options-xp.jpg" alt="Disable hibernation Power options XP" width="404" height="454" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h4>Windows 7</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Navigate to the Advanced power settings dialog\r\n<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Win+R -&gt; "control powercfg.cpl,,1"</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Control Panel\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to<strong> Control Panel -&gt; Power Options</strong> or <strong>Win+R -&gt; "powercfg.cpl"</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Change plan settings</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Change advanced power settings</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-494" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/disable-hiber-advanced-power-win7.jpg" alt="Disable hibernation Advanced Power options Win7" width="418" height="449" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Sleep -&gt; Allow hybrid sleep</strong></li>\r\n<li>Set to <strong>Off</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Sleep -&gt; Hibernate after</strong></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Set to <strong>Never</strong> (enter 0)</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-495" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/disable-hiber-advanced-power-win7-after.jpg" alt="Disable hibernation Advanced Power options Win7 after" width="418" height="449" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>III. Then check if the C:\\hyberfil.sys is removed or remove it manually</h3>', 'Disable Hibernation and Delete hyberfil.sys', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'disable-hibernation-and-delete-hyberfil-sys', '', '', '2015-03-28 21:11:37', '2015-03-28 21:11:37', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=492', 0, 'post', '', 0),
