(513, 1, '2015-03-28 21:40:54', '2015-03-28 21:40:54', '<p>1. Press <strong>Win+R</strong> or <strong>Win+R -&gt; "cmd"</strong> </p>\r\n<p>2. To <strong>start</strong> a service use </p>\r\n<pre>sc start [service-name] </pre>\r\n<p>3. To <strong>stop</strong> a service use </p>\r\n<pre>sc stop [service-name] </pre>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-516" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/manage-services-run.jpg" alt="Manage services Run" width="427" height="236" /></p>\r\n<p>4. To create a shortcut </p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to <strong>Desktop</strong> </li>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Context menu</strong> select <strong>New -&gt; Shortcut</strong> </li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Enter command in the location field</p>\r\n<pre>sc start|stop [service-name] </pre>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-515" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/manage-services-new-shortcut.jpg" alt="Manage services New shortcut" width="628" height="459" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Enter a name </li>\r\n<li>Save </li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Use it as an icon or set a <strong>Keyboard shortcut</strong> in its <strong>Properties</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-514" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/manage-services-key-shortcut.jpg" alt="Manage services key shortcut" width="437" height="589" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Manage Services With Command Line', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'manage-services-with-command-line', '', '', '2015-03-28 21:40:54', '2015-03-28 21:40:54', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=513', 0, 'post', '', 0),
