(681, 1, '2015-03-31 17:50:21', '2015-03-31 17:50:21', '<p>If there is <strong>PHP error</strong></p>\r\n<pre>Fatal error: Maximum execution time of 60 seconds exceeded</pre>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-684" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/max-exec-time.png" alt="Max exec time error" width="740" height="436" /></p>\r\n<p>follow these steps to disable it</p>\r\n<p>1. Open file <em><strong>wp-includes/functions.php</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>2. Find a line in the <em>wp_get_htttp()</em> function</p>\r\n<pre>@set_time_limit( 60 );</pre>\r\n<p>3. Comment it.</p>\r\n<p>4. Also it may be necessary to set <strong>PHP directives</strong> for the max time in the<em><strong> php.ini</strong></em></p>\r\n<pre>max_execution_time\r\nmax_input_time</pre>\r\n<p>5. Then <strong>restart</strong> the server.</p>\r\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-685" src="http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/max-exec-time-success.png" alt="Max exec time success" width="423" height="121" /></p>', 'Solution to Importer Maximum Execution Time', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'solution-to-importer-maximum-execution-time', '', '', '2015-03-31 17:50:21', '2015-03-31 17:50:21', '', 0, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/?p=681', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(684, 1, '2015-03-31 17:48:09', '2015-03-31 17:48:09', '', 'Max exec time error', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'max-exec-time', '', '', '2015-03-31 17:48:26', '2015-03-31 17:48:26', '', 681, 'http://pcadvice.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/max-exec-time.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
